\'95 Linker Problem\
\
The linker in Leopard's GCC has a bit of a problem with some libraries, notably X11's libGL.  When trying to link libGL (for example), it spits back an error:\
\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural

\f1\fs20 \cf0 ld: cycle in dylib re-exports with /usr/X11/lib/libGL.dylib for architecture i386\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural

\f0\fs24 \cf0 \
The standard workaround for this is to link using the 
\f1\fs20 -dylib_file
\f0\fs24  flag, which tells the linker where the library 
\i really
\i0  is:\
\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural

\f1\fs20 \cf0 -dylib_file /usr/X11/lib/libGL.dylib:/usr/X11/lib/libGL.dylib\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural

\f0\fs24 \cf0 \
Notice that both paths are the same, this is just how the workaround operates.  This causes some undefined symbol errors, so 
\f1\fs20 -undefined dynamic_lookup
\f0\fs24  is also needed.\
\
To get libGL to work in GRASS, before configuring, edit 
\f1\fs20 include/Make/Platform.make.in
\f0\fs24  and change the 
\f1\fs20 OPENGLLIB=
\f0\fs24  line to:\
\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural

\f1\fs20 \cf0 OPENGLLIB = -dylib_file /usr/X11/lib/libGL.dylib:/usr/X11/lib/libGL.dylib -undefined dynamic_lookup\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural

\f0\fs24 \cf0 \
It may be necessary to change this in configure, or configure will fail to locate libGL.  I don't want to go into a lot of detail, but replace all "-lGL" with the above dylib_file string.\
